<task id="102" project="spaarkeai-compose-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>File ADR-013 amendment (Path B per CLAUDE.md §6.5) — widened facade for document-context</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>0.5 hour</estimated-effort>
    <tags>adr, documentation, adr-conflict-resolution, path-b</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <dependencies>095</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <phase>10-polish</phase>
    <supplement-spec>spec-supplement-2026-07-01-three-pane-pivot.md ADR Tension section</supplement-spec>
    <governance>CLAUDE.md §6.5 ADR Conflict Resolution Protocol Path B</governance>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    File an ADR-013 amendment that formalizes the widened
    `IInvokePlaybookAi` facade contract (task 095).

    Steps:
      1. Read the refined ADR-013 concise at `.claude/adr/ADR-013-bff-ai-extraction.md`
      2. Read the full ADR at `docs/adr/ADR-013-bff-ai-extraction.md`
      3. Add an amendment section to the full ADR:

         ## Amendment 2026-07-01 — Document-context invocation

         The refined facade `IInvokePlaybookAi` MAY accept optional
         document-context arguments (`userContext`, `Document`) for
         consumers that dispatch playbooks against a specific document.
         This preserves the CRUD/AI boundary while supporting document-
         scoped analysis flows.

         **Motivating consumer**: `spaarkeai-compose-r1` — Compose
         dispatches whole-document + selection-scoped AI functions
         (Summarize / Rewrite / Find Similar / etc.) that require the
         playbook to receive the source document's plain text (or a
         structured DocumentContext).

         **Before**: `InvokePlaybookAsync(playbookId, parameters, context, ct)`
         — parameter-only invocation. Suitable for M365 Copilot Agent
         path (Copilot supplies document context via conversation
         attachments outside the facade).

         **After**: Optional `userContext: string?` and `document:
         DocumentContext?` overload. The facade forwards these to
         `PlaybookRunRequest.UserContext` and `PlaybookRunRequest.Document`.
         Existing parameter-only callers are unaffected.

         **Boundary preserved**: CRUD code (Compose endpoints) STILL
         only injects `IInvokePlaybookAi` + `IConsumerRoutingService` —
         NEVER `IPlaybookOrchestrationService` or `IOpenAiClient`.

      4. Update the concise ADR (.claude/adr/) with a summary of the
         amendment
      5. Update `.claude/adr/INDEX.md` if it lists amendments
      6. Append a note to `projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/notes/defer-issues.md`
         under an "ADR-013 amendment (2026-07-01 — path B)" section
      7. Add an entry to `.claude/CHANGELOG.md` referencing the amendment

    Rationale (for the PR description):
      Per CLAUDE.md §6.5, Path B is the correct resolution when an ADR's
      prior decision is no longer optimal AND a facade extension is
      cleaner than bypassing it. Path A (project-scoped exception) would
      set a bad precedent — every future document-context consumer would
      need to declare its own exception. Path B lands the amendment once
      and the facade permanently supports the class of use case.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    ADR maintainer / architectural governance engineer. Follows
    CLAUDE.md §6.5 protocol precisely.
  </role>

  <goal>
    ADR-013 amendment filed. Concise ADR updated. INDEX + CHANGELOG
    reflect the amendment. defer-issues.md documents the R1-scope amendment.
    Future consumers can invoke document-context playbooks without ADR
    friction.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="claudemd-protocol">CLAUDE.md § 6.5</file>
